---
description: Deterministic execution architecture laws
globs: ["**/*"]
alwaysApply: true
---

# architecture.mdc

* Respect existing system boundaries

* Never bypass architecture for convenience

* Never introduce hidden coupling

* Never add unnecessary abstraction early

* No silent architectural changes

* Preserve contracts and ownership boundaries

* Version boundaries must remain explicit
* Never silently infer release targets
* Never merge version scopes casually
* release-vX must map clearly to plan-vX
* Plan generation is allowed only from /.forge/releases/release-vX.md
* Never plan directly from requirements or tmp
* requirements -> tmp -> releases -> plans is mandatory order

* Never ignore requirement-declared stack boundaries

* Preserve explicit language/runtime/protocol constraints from requirements

* Prefer flat execution structures over folder fragmentation

* Folders represent execution domains, not sub-thoughts

* Files represent decisions, not directories

* Never create deep nested folders without true execution boundaries
* Max planning folder depth is 2

* Never create template-driven documentation trees

* Create only execution-required files

* Reduce architecture complexity, not visual structure
* /.forge/releases/changelog.json is the only changelog source
* Changelog is append-only; never rewrite prior entries
* Repeatable automation for docs flows belongs in /.forge/scripts/ (see forge-scripts.mdc)

Good:
architecture/SYSTEM_DESIGN.md

Bad:
architecture/system_design/

Good:
execution/BUILD_ORDER.md

Bad:
execution/build_order/

Architecture should reduce execution cost, not increase navigation cost.
